--- !u!114 &3565468141906147812
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 9073611175433636603}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: fbeb6d65be27d3b40a131a1e4ace56b5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  steps:
  - message: 'Gizmo, I need your help! '
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 1
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Hello, {player}! What happened?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "I am now fixing the hovercraft because I finished the pre-test. These
      hover brackets don\u2019t align. My measurements must be wrong, the craft will
      never stabilize."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 1
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: I see the problem here. Today we will master physical quantities, units,
      and measurement errors. With consistency, your hover frame will fit together
      properly.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Ahh, so, what exactly are physical quantities first?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 1
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: They are properties we can measure, {player}. It includes length, mass,
      electric current, amount of substance luminous intensity, and time.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 1
    endTime: 2
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Okay, so what are those first six quantities?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: First is the length. It shows dimension and answers how long, how far,
      how thick, or how high something is. It is measured in meters.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 2
    endTime: 3
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "While mass denotes how heavy an object is\u2014the quantity of matter
      directly proportional to size. Note that its unit is kilograms."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 3
    endTime: 4
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Third is the Electric Current. It is the rate of flow of electricity,
      moving continuously in a certain direction through a medium. Unit is the ampere
      (A).\r"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Another one is the Amount of Substance tells how much matter makes up
      an object, closely connected with mass. Measured in moles (mol).
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 5
    endTime: 6
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: The, Luminous Intensity is the brightness exerted by a source, or the
      amount of light it gives off. Unit is the candela (cd).
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 6
    endTime: 7
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: And lastly, Time shows change in a quantifiable limit. It always moves
      forward, observed differently depending on perspective. Unit is seconds (s).
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 7
    endTime: 8
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: " Great, I\u2019ve got the six. Thanks to you, Gizmo! But what about
      the errors you mentioned?"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 8
    endTime: 9
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: 'There are two main errors exist: Random errors scatter results unpredictably;
      Systematic errors deviate consistently because of faulty instruments or biased
      methods.'
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 9
    endTime: 10
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: So if I recalibrate tools and repeat measurements, I reduce both types
      of error?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Right! With consistent units, accurate definitions, and minimized errors,
      your hover frame aligns correctly at last.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Thank you very much, Gizmo! Now I understand them well!
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 10
    endTime: 11
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Welcome! Now you get it, let's test what you've learned by answering
      the quiz haha!
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
